<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-07-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-07-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="705" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d705">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Merry</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">San
                                        Salvador</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-07-18"><hi rend="italic">July 18,
                                1906</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Merry states that the instructions in Mr. Bacon’s telegram of the
                            17th have been carefully noted, and that the Nicaraguan Government has
                            appointed a native representative. Mr. Merry also states that his
                            representation of Costa Rica is pro forma and that he will telegraph
                            from San Jose and Guatemala on conclusion.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>